#change type formats and change the data names to lowercase letters
d2 <- d2%>%
  mutate(Age.group=tolower(Age.group))%>%
  mutate(Race.and.Hispanic.Origin.Group=tolower(Race.and.Hispanic.Origin.Group))%>%
  mutate(COVID.19.Deaths=as.numeric(COVID.19.Deaths))%>%
  mutate(Total.Deaths=as.numeric(Total.Deaths))%>%
  mutate(Pneumonia.Deaths=as.numeric(Pneumonia.Deaths))%>%
  mutate(Pneumonia.and.COVID.19.Deaths=as.numeric(Pneumonia.and.COVID.19.Deaths))%>%
  mutate(Influenza.Deaths=as.numeric(Influenza.Deaths))%>%
  mutate(Pneumonia.and.COVID.19.Deaths=as.numeric(Pneumonia.and.COVID.19.Deaths))

d1 <-d1%>%
  mutate(Number.of.COVID.19.Deaths=as.numeric(Number.of.COVID.19.Deaths))%>%
  mutate(Age.Group=as.factor(Age.Group))%>%
  mutate(Age.Group=tolower(Age.Group))%>%
  mutate(Condition=as.factor(Condition))%>%
  mutate(Condition=tolower(Condition))

#calculate number of deaths divided by total population
d1$death_popu <-d1$Number.of.COVID.19.Deaths/330122380
d2$death_popu <-d2$COVID.19.Deaths/330122380

#calculate death rate (deaths/population)*1000
d1$death_rate <-d1$death_popu*1000
d2$death_rate <-d2$death_popu *1000


#Linear Regression 
#simple linear regression of count ~ temperature

death.condition<-lm(death_rate ~ Condition, data= d1)
#show the summary
summary(death.condition)  #p-value: 5.305e-10
